cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes an image-based localization system that relies on capturing and indexing distinctive local features in ground textures. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as the proposed system can be used for robot localization. The paper also involves machine learning techniques for image processing, which makes it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it involves the analysis of ground textures.
